./sdp/verification/t-001@20260408t223256z-verify.md:31:Minor gap: `narrative_prose` is a 10th category in `CATEGORY_KEYWORDS` (added alongside this work) but is absent from `ollama`'s `DEFAULT_FITNESS`. When queried, `get_fitness("ollama", "narrative_prose")` returns the fallback `0.5`. This is acceptable — the spec required 9 categories and the task predates `narrative_prose` — but the inconsistency with cloud agents (claude/codex/gemini all have `narrative_prose`) means ollama is at an implicit disadvantage for narrative tasks.
./sdp/verification/t-001@20260408t223256z-verify.md:33:`ollama` is intentionally absent from `DEFAULT_AGENTS`, so it will not appear in `select_pair()` or standard rotation without being passed explicitly via `available_agents`. This is a design choice, not a bug, but worth documenting for downstream integrators.
